Sure! To write an if/then statement in C, you need to use the if keyword followed by a condition enclosed in parentheses. If the condition evaluates to true, the code within the curly braces will be executed. Here's an example:

```
if (age >= 18) {
    printf("You are eligible to vote.");
}
```

In this example, the if statement checks if the age variable is greater than or equal to 18. If it is, the code within the curly braces will be executed, which in this case is a printf statement that prints "You are eligible to vote."
